data.chText: （建筑物里的物品、家具等的）清单；财产清单
data.enText: a written list of all the objects, furniture, etc. in a particular building
an inventory of the museum's contents
all the goods in a shop

data.chText: 在未来的十二个星期中将进行清仓处理。
data.enText: The inventory will be disposed of over the next twelve weeks.
to make a complete list of sth

data.chText: 我把父亲收藏的图片列成了清单。
data.enText: I've inventoried my father's collection of prints.

simple_means.memory_skill: in 进入 + vent 来 + ory 表物 → 进来的〔全部财产〕→ 财产清单

means: (建筑物里的物品、家具等的)清单

tr: making an itemized list of merchandise or supplies on hand
example: an inventory may be necessary to see if anything is missing
they held an inventory every month

tr: the merchandise that a shop has on hand
example: they carried a vast inventory of hardware
they stopped selling in exact sizes in order to reduce inventory
he dipped into his intellectual armory to find an answer

tr: a detailed list of all the items in stock
(accounting) the value of a firm's current assets including raw materials and work in progress and finished goods
make or include in an itemized record or report
example: Inventory all books before the end of the year

value.def: An inventory is a written list of all the objects in a particular place.

example.ex: Before starting, he made an inventory of everything that was to stay.
example.tran: 开始之前,他把所有要留下的东西列了详细的清单。

value.def: An inventory is a supply or stock of something.

example.ex: ...one inventory of twelve sails for each yacht.
example.tran: 每艘快艇 12 张帆的储备

adventur〔e〕冒险 + ous 有…性质的，关于…的 → 爱冒险的
a 加强 + ven 来 + ue → 让人们可以走来走去 → 大路
contra 反对；相反；对比 + ven 来 + e → 反着来 → 违反
con 共同 + ven 来 + e → 都来到一起 → 召集
con 共同 + ven 来 + ience 表状态 → 全部能来没有障碍 → 方便
con 共同 + vent 来 + ion 表名词 → 大家来到一起 → 集会

partsOfSpeech.d: 发生许多事情的；多变故的
